LAGOS – The Lagos State Police Command said it has arrested one Adigun Ganiyu, 26 , and another traffic robbers who specialises in robbing unsuspecting members of the society. In a statement released by the Commands spokesman , DSP Elkana Bala, the robbers were arrested by a team of Policemen from Okokomaiko Police Station while on patrol. The Police said the suspects were intercepted by the Policemen on surveillance patrol on May 17, 2019 at about 10:20pm at Cassidy bus stop. Okokomaiko. “The hoodlums engaged the Police in a gun battle but eventually succumbed to the superior power of the Police as one of the hoodlums was fatally injured. “Recovered from the gang includes, one Double barrel gun with one live cartridge and two expanded cartridges. The gang’s operational motorcycle used robbery was also recovered. The suspect who is presently helping investigators with useful information about his fleeing colleagues has however confessed that their gang is responsible for series of traffic robbery along Okokomaiko. In a related development, the Operatives atached to Ilemba Hausa Police Station, also intercepted a gang of traffic robbery suspects operating on motorcycle along Church bus stop Ilemba. The suspected robber and his gangs on May18, 2019 at about 2030hrs were shooting sporadically when one Justice Igboanusi , 29 of no 11 Jinadu Street , Ajangbadi was nabbed by the Police. One short double barrels gun with one live cartridge was recovered from him while other gang members escaped. The Command however said investigation is ongoing and the suspects will be charged to Court at it conclusion.